## 19. Variable Selection Rationale

The variables selected for modeling are tied directly to the research questions and to the student-success decision context. **FinalGrade** is selected as the outcome because it directly measures academic performance. Variables related to earlier grades, absences, finances, support-service usage, enrollment context, and engagement are retained because they represent information a university could use to identify students who may need support.

**StudentID** is excluded because it is an identifier and has no meaningful relationship to the student-success process. Centering, scaling, and one-hot encoding are not applied on this EDA page because they are model-preparation steps. They will be handled in the modeling workflow where algorithm requirements differ.

